      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Assignment: Build a Chatbot using Hugging Face Transformers\n",
        "\n",
        "## Objective\n",
        "Build a simple conversational chatbot using a pre-trained transformer model from Hugging Face that can interact with users and generate meaningful responses.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Tools and Technologies\n",
        "- **Python**\n",
        "- **Hugging Face Transformers**\n",
        "- **PyTorch**\n",
        "- **Jupyter Notebook**\n",
        "\n",
        "## Task Description\n",
        "This notebook implements a console-based (interactive) chatbot using the **DialoGPT-medium** model. The model is fine-tuned on conversational data and can generate context-aware responses."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Install the necessary libraries if not already installed\n",
        "# !pip install transformers torch"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "from transformers import AutoModelForCausalLM, AutoTokenizer\n",
        "import torch\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. Model Loading (Mandatory)\n",
        "# Load a pre-trained transformer model from Hugging Face\n",
        "# We use 'microsoft/DialoGPT-medium' for better response quality\n",
        "model_name = \"microsoft/DialoGPT-medium\"\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Loading model and tokenizer... This may take a few minutes for the first time.\")\n",
        "tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(model_name)\n",
        "model = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(model_name)\n",
        "print(\"Model loaded successfully!\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def run_chatbot():\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Main function to handle user interaction and generate responses.\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    print(\"Chatbot: Hello! I am your AI assistant. How can I help you today?\")\n",
        "    print(\"(Type 'exit' or 'quit' to end the conversation)\")\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Initialize chat history\n",
        "    # We need this to maintain the context of the conversation\n",
        "    chat_history_ids = None\n",
        "\n",
        "    while True:\n",
        "        # 2. User Input Handling\n",
        "        user_input = input(\"User: \")\n",
        "        \n",
        "        # 5. Exit Condition\n",
        "        if user_input.lower() in [\"exit\", \"quit\"]:\n",
        "            print(\"Chatbot: Goodbye! Feel free to ask more questions anytime.\")\n",
        "            break\n",
        "            \n",
        "        # 3. Response Generation (using prompt-based generation)\n",
        "        # Tokenize user input and append the end-of-sentence token\n",
        "        new_user_input_ids = tokenizer.encode(user_input + tokenizer.eos_token, return_tensors='pt')\n",
        "        \n",
        "        # 4. Continuous Conversation (Maintaining context)\n",
        "        # Append the new user input tokens to the chat history\n",
        "        if chat_history_ids is not None:\n",
        "            bot_input_ids = torch.cat([chat_history_ids, new_user_input_ids], dim=-1)\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            bot_input_ids = new_user_input_ids\n",
        "        \n",
        "        # Refined parameters for much more logical and coherent responses\n",
        "        chat_history_ids = model.generate(\n",
        "            bot_input_ids, \n",
        "            max_length=1000, \n",
        "            pad_token_id=tokenizer.eos_token_id,\n",
        "            no_repeat_ngram_size=3,\n",
        "            do_sample=True, \n",
        "            top_k=100, \n",
        "            top_p=0.7,\n",
        "            temperature=0.6, # Lower temperature for less randomness\n",
        "            repetition_penalty=1.2, # Added penalty for repetitive loops\n",
        "            attention_mask=torch.ones(bot_input_ids.shape, dtype=torch.long) # Required for newer PyTorch/Transformers\n",
        "        )\n",
        "        \n",
        "        # Decode and print only the bot's newly generated tokens\n",
        "        bot_response = tokenizer.decode(chat_history_ids[:, bot_input_ids.shape[-1]:][0], skip_special_tokens=True)\n",
        "        \n",
        "        # Display the output\n",
        "        print(f\"Chatbot: {bot_response}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n",
        "    run_chatbot()"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Implementation Notes\n",
        "1. **Model**: DialoGPT-medium is a state-of-the-art conversational model pre-trained on Reddit discussion threads.\n",
        "2. **Context Management**: The `chat_history_ids` variable stores the entire conversation sequence, allowing the model to \"remember\" previous exchanges.\n",
        "3. **Generation Strategy**: \n",
        "   - `do_sample=True`: Enables stochastic generation for more diverse responses.\n",
        "   - `temperature=0.6`: Lowered to improve consistency and reduce nonsense.\n",
        "   - `repetition_penalty=1.2`: Specifically discourages the model from getting stuck in loops (like the common 'cat' loop).\n",
        "   - `no_repeat_ngram_size=3`: Prevents the model from repeating simple three-word phrases."
      ]
    }
  ],\n",
